WKT: The occupiers began mass-deporting residents of the village of Popivka in the Luhansk region and settling their soldiers there.

No one asks the local population about their desire to leave, where they will be taken and where they will be housed in the middle of winter, too. In principle, the Russians don't care. The main thing is to free up homes for their soldiers, OVA reported.
